Body:
Description: Hi Support,

Here's an issue reported by Ardentec,[Ardentec] The field "filepath" of  Share with Sensitive Contenct showing nothing at all as attached screenshot.
Please assist in clarifying it and make it clear.

Jimmy
What We've Learned Updated: APAC Timezone

Steps to Reproduce Updated: Step 1: Navigate to File System Job Group and run SEEK job (collects Sensitive Data). The data should contain some exceptions like password protected or without read rights etc.
Step 2: View the results tab and it will not display the path of those files.

What We've Learned Updated: The customer has upgraded to v.11.6.125 and afterwards ran the SEEK job (sensitive data discovery job) for file systems. However, for some of the entries in the reports, they dont see any data for the file path being scanned. This is a known bug and has been resolved in v.11.6.131 and v.11.6.132.
Next Steps Updated: Customer has been informed to update the version of NEA. Awaiting a response now from customer end.

What We've Learned Updated: The customer has upgraded to v.11.6.125 and afterwards ran the SEEK job (sensitive data discovery job) for file systems. However, for some of the entries in the reports, they dont see any data for the file path being scanned. This is a known bug for files that have exceptions like being password protected and has been resolved in v.11.6.127 and v.11.6.132.

As per latest update and screenshot image, they are able to see data in FileSystem Solution -> 0.Collection -> 0-Collection-> FSDLP_Matchesview but not in 7.Sensitive Data reports. This is reproducible in my lab.

Next Steps Updated: Awaiting DEV response.

Steps to Reproduce Updated: Step 1: Navigate to File System Job Group and run 0.Collection and SEEK job (collects Sensitive Data). 
Step 2: View FileSystem Solution -> 0.Collection -> 0-Collection-> FSDLP_Matchesview
Step 3: Navigate to 7.Sensitive Data and then execute the FS_DLPResults and view reports.

What We've Learned Updated: The customer has upgraded to v.11.6.125 and afterwards ran the SEEK job (sensitive data discovery job) for file systems. However, for some of the entries in the reports, they dont see any data for the file path being scanned. This is a known bug for files that have exceptions like being password protected and has been resolved in v.11.6.127 and v.11.6.132.

Customer has upgraded to 11.6.0.130.
As per latest update and screenshot image, they are able to see data in FileSystem Solution -> 0.Collection -> 0-Collection-> FSDLP_Matchesview but not in 7.Sensitive Data reports. This is reproducible in my lab.
